Description: The incredibly popular manga series that spawned an anime series, stage musicals and countless imitators gets a new printing.
Title: SAILOR MOON, VOL. 1
Author: Naoko Takeuchi

Description: A predecessor to "Sailor Moon," this collection of stories has never before been printed in the United States.
Title: CODENAME: SAILOR V, Vol. 1
Author: Naoko Takeuchi

Description: Troubled by spirits that only he can see, Watanuki Kimiharo strikes a Faustian bargain with an alluring witch to get rid of them.
Title: XXXHOLIC, VOL. 17
Author: Clamp

Description: Ichigo Kurosaki sees dead people and must help usher them safely into the afterlife. In this volume, a look at how "soul catching" was done 100 years ago.
Title: BLEACH, VOL. 36
Author: Tite Kubo

Description: Naruto meets a former classmate and must face-off with him... to the death!
Title: NARUTO, VOL. 52
Author: Masashi Kishimoto

Description: Misao Harada can see into a magical realm where she is the bride demon of prophecy. In the volume, the truth about a past incident is revealed, but is it worth the pain it will cause?
Title: BLACK BIRD, VOL. 10
Author: Kanoko Sakurakoji

Description: Monkey D. Luffy and his motley crew of would-be pirates search for a legendary treasure called “One Piece.” In this volume, the Navy looks to squash the pirate rebellion once and for all.
Title: ONE PIECE, VOL. 58
Author: Eiichiro Oda

Description: Amu is granted magical powers after making a wish to become a more popular and outgoing person.
Title: SHUGO CHARA!, Vol.12
Author: Peach-Pit

Description: Ultimo and Vice are the embodiment of good and evil. In this installment, meet Jealousy and Rune!
Title: ULTIMO, VOL. 6
Author: Hiroyuki Takei

Description: After the death of her brother, Teru Kurebayashi has been receiving comforting messages from Daisy, who communicates through her brother’s cell phone. In this installment, Teru gets kidnapped.
Title: DENGEKI DAISY, VOL. 6
Author: Kyousuke Motomi
